com.phunware.engagement.log

Class Logging

  • com.phunware.engagement.log.Logging

  • public class Logging

    API for sending log output.

    Generally, use the Log.v() Log.d() Log.i() Log.w() Log.e() and Log.wtf() methods.

    The order in terms of verbosity, from least to most is TERRIBLE_FAILURE, ERROR, WARN, INFO, DEBUG, VERBOSE. Verbose should never be compiled into an application except during development.

    Tip: A good convention is to declare a TAG constant in your class: 

    private static final String TAG = "LocationManagerImpl";
     and use that in subsequent calls to the log methods.
